      "content": "Wait, what do you mean by \"goblin hoarding all the bits\"? That's a weird way to put it. \n\nAnyway, regarding the instrumentation—since I'm on a constrained ECU, I can't exactly run Valgrind or some heavy profiler. If I try to implement a custom wrapper for `operator new` to track allocations, what specific metrics should I be logging to catch these slow leaks without blowing out my own memory overhead? I need to find the specific call sites that aren't being paired with a `delete`.",
      "source": "evaluator"
